claim.claim-text:
1. A high-frequency signal transmission line comprising:
an element assembly having a first relative dielectric constant and having a first principal surface and a second principal surface;
a line-shaped signal line provided within the element assembly;
a first ground conductor provided in the element assembly and on the first principal surface side with respect to the signal line and facing the signal line, the first ground conductor being provided with a first opening that overlaps the signal line; and
a first high dielectric constant layer having a second relative dielectric constant higher than the first relative dielectric constant and provided on the first principal surface so as to overlap the first opening.

7. An electronic device comprising:
a component; and
a high-frequency signal transmission line comprising:
an element assembly having a first relative dielectric constant and having a first principal surface and a second principal surface;
a line-shaped signal line provided within the element assembly;
a first ground conductor provided in the element assembly and on the first principal surface side with respect to the signal line and facing the signal line, the first ground conductor being provided with a first opening that overlaps the signal line;
a second ground conductor facing the first ground conductor across the signal line in the element assembly; and
a first high dielectric constant layer having a second relative dielectric constant higher than the first relative dielectric constant and provided on the first principal surface so as to overlap with first opening; wherein

the high-frequency signal transmission line is disposed such that the second principal surface contacts with the component.
